data.rdfs:label: nano-cap analysis of gene expression evidence
data.rdfs:comment: NanoCAGE captures the 5' ends of molecules by template switching. When polymerizing the cDNA of a capped mRNA, the reverse transcriptase adds extra cytosines that are complementary to the cap. Each 5' full length cDNAs is extended upon hybridization of the riboguanosine-tailed template switching oligonucleotides to these extra cytosines. In semisuppressive PCR, the short templates fold intramolecularly and prevent the binding of primers, which precludes amplification; longer molecules are less likely to fold and are thus amplified. Templates derived from reaction artifacts form stable homoduplexes, also precluding amplification. After template switching, semisuppressive PCR, and EcoP151 cleavage, 25-bp tags are ligated to bar code-containing oligonucleotide adaptors. After PCR amplification, the nanoCAGE tags are sequenced by synthesis. NanoCAGE requires as little as 10 nanograms of total RNA.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of transcript expression evidence based on high-throughput (HT) sequencing of the 5' ends of cDNA molecules that are selected by reverse transcriptase template switching.

data.rdfs:label: RNA-seq evidence
data.rdfs:comment: Total RNA is isolated from cells and mRNA is purified by targeting the 3' polyadenylated (poly(A)) tail with poly(T) oligos covalently attached to a substrate. Next, cDNA fragments are generated either by hydrolysis of RNA into 200-300 base oligonucleotides, preceded by reverse transcription, or by reverse transcription initiated by random primers. The cDNA second strand is synthesized, fragments are adapter ligated and high-throughput sequencing is performed by Roche 454, Illumina, ABI-SOLiD, or another HT sequencing technology. Resulting sort reads are aligned against a reference genome, and downstream analysis is performed.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of transcript expression evidence based on high-throughput (HT) sequencing of fragmented cDNA molecules.

data.rdfs:label: chromatin immunoprecipitation evidence

DNA and proteins are chemically cross-linked in vivo to form chromatin complexes, followed by cell lysis and DNA shearing. Fragmented DNA-protein complexes are selectively enriched for a protein of interest using a specific antibody (immunoprecipitation). Protein digestion and DNA purification are performed prior to DNA detection via molecular cloning and sequencing, polymerase chain reaction (PCR), microarray analysis (ChIP-on-chip), or direct high-throughput sequencing (ChIP-seq).
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of immunoprecipitation evidence that is used to identify a protein binding site on a genomic DNA sequence.

where nucleic acid that has been bound to protein is cleaved with 1,10-phenanthroline-copper complex resulting in a high-resolution footprint of sequence-specific protein-DNA contacts.

data.rdfs:label: in vivo deubiquitination assay evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of in vivo deubiquitination assay evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: curator inference
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of inferential evidence that is based on a conclusion drawn by a curator.

data.rdfs:label: in vitro transcription assay evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of in vitro assay evidence where transcription is detected in vitro to validate the activation or repression ablity of a transcription factor in the absence of other proteins present in in vivo conditions.

data.rdfs:label: CpG island microarray evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of evidence arising from a CpG island microarray experiment that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: in vitro demethylation assay evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of in vitro demethylation assay evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: cap analysis of gene expression evidence
data.rdfs:comment: Complementary DNA (cDNA) is synthesized from microgram quantities of mRNA using first-strand cDNA primer (oligo dT12-18) and reverse transcriptase in the presence of trehalose and sorbitol, followed by selection of full-length cDNA with biotinylated cap-trapper. Linkers are attached to the 5' ends of full-length enriched cDNAs to introduce a recognition site for the restriction endonuclease MmeI, which creates a two base overhang. After amplification, sequencing tags are concatenated for high-throughput sequencing. Resulting sort reads are aligned against a reference genome, and downstream analysis is performed.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of transcript expression evidence based on high-throughput (HT) sequencing of the 5' ends of cDNA molecules that are selected by a cap-trapper system.

data.rdfs:label: match to InterPro member signature evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A match to InterPro member signature evidence that is employed in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: mammalian 2-hybrid assay evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of mammalian 2-hybrid assay evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: eTag assay evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of eTag assay evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: similarity evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: Similarity evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: lipid binding assay evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of lipid binding assay evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: manual assertion
data.rdfs:comment: A manual assertion could be based on evidence that is generated by and interpreted by a human or it could involve human review of computationally generated information.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: An assertion method that involves human review.

data.rdfs:label: differential hybridization evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of differential hybridization experiment that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: visual sequence inspection evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of inference from background scientific knowledge used in manual assertion based on the visual inspection of promoter region to identify putative binding sites.

data.rdfs:label: methidiumpropyl-ethylenediaminetetraacetic acid iron (II) footprinting evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of nucleic acid binding evidence where the synthetic molecule methidiumpropyl-EDTA (MPE) is used to cleave ligand-protected DNA, followed by analysis of the restriction fragments to generate a footprint (i.e. size and location) of small molecule binding sites on the DNA.

data.rdfs:label: in vivo desumoylation assay evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of in vivo desumoylation assay evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: epistatic interaction evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: Used when an annotation is based on results of epistatis analysis of an allele of the gene in question and a mutant allele at another locus.

data.rdfs:label: author statement
data.obo:IAO_0000115: An evidence type that is based on an assertion by the author of a paper, which is read by a curator.

data.rdfs:label: cDNA microarray evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of evidence arising from a cDNA microarray experiment that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: in vitro defarnesylation assay evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of in vitro defarnesylation assay evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: in vitro polyADP-ribosylation assay evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of in vitro assay evidence where ADP-ribosylated residues in proteins are detected in an in vitro experiment.

data.rdfs:label: phage display evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of phage display evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: sequence orthology evidence used in automatic assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: Sequence orthology evidence that is employed in an automatic assertion.

data.rdfs:label: non-traceable author statement
data.rdfs:comment: The non-traceable author statement evidence code should be used in all cases where the author makes a statement that a curator wants to capture but for which there are neither results presented nor a specific reference cited in the source used to make the annotation. The source of the information may be peer reviewed papers, textbooks, database records or vouchered specimens.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: An author statement that is not associated with results presented or a cited reference.

data.rdfs:label: Sos-recruitment assay evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of physical interaction evidence that is based on a genetic screening system that detects protein-protein interactions and is not based on a transcriptional readout.

data.rdfs:label: genetic interaction evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of genetic interaction experiment evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: heterologous protein expression evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of protein expression evidence where a gene from one cell is inserted into a cell that does not typically contain that gene and heterologous protein expression is assessed.
data.oboInOwl:hasRelatedSynonym: IDA: protein expression in heterologous system

data.rdfs:label: DNA synthesis cell proliferation assay evidence
in vivo transcription assay evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of in vivo transcription assay evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: Northwestern blot evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: Used when an annotation is made based on a Northwestern blot analysis, which detects RNA binding of proteins using labeled RNA as probe hybridizing to electrophoretically separated proteins.

data.rdfs:label: evidence based on computational logical inference used in automatic assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of evidence based on computational logical inference that is used in automatic assertion.

data.rdfs:label: in vivo protein kinase assay evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of in vivo assay evidence where phosphorylated residues in a protein are detected in cells in vivo.

data.rdfs:label: combinatorial evidence
data.rdfs:comment: A key aspect of this type of evidence is that two or more pieces of information are combined to generate an emergent type of evidence not possible with the constituent pieces of evidence alone. A combinatorial analysis typically involves incorporation of different types of evidence.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of evidence that arises out of the integration of more than one line of evidence.

data.rdfs:label: expression library screen evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of expression library screen evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: voucher specimen analysis evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: Used when an annotation is made on the basis of for a phenotype description for a species or higher level group that given by an author who explicitly references an observation of a voucher specimen(s). Voucher specimens are defined as those specimens with permanent museum catalog numbers. Thus it would be possible for a person to examine this particular specimen and observe the annotated phenotype.

data.rdfs:label: radioimmunoassay evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of radioimmunoassay evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: nucleotide analog incorporation evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of nucleotide analog incorporation evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: immunoprecipitation evidence
data.rdfs:comment: Transcription factors isolated in this way can be incubated with a radiolabeled probe to demonstrate binding.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of protein assay evidence that involves precipitation of a multivalent antigen by a bivalent antibody for protein isolation.

data.rdfs:label: morphological similarity evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: Used when an annotation is made based on the similarity of the shape, structure or overall configuration of structures.

data.rdfs:label: motility wound healing assay evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of motility wound healing assay evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: microscopy evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of direct assay evidence where a microscope was used to view a sample.

data.rdfs:label: resonant mirror biosensor evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of resonant mirror biosensor evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: bacterial one-hybrid evidence
data.rdfs:comment: Bacterial one-hybrid assay is a method for screening a library of candidate proteins (prey plasmid) for the ability to bind to a target, cis-regulatory element or any other short, DNA binding sequence placed 5' to reporter genes (bait plasmid). Transformation of a bacterial host with two different plasmids is required: One is designed to express the "bait". The other plasmid contains a "prey" which, if bound to by the chimeric fusion product, drives expression of downstream reporter genes.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of hybrid interaction evidence that uses bacterial transformation with two plasmids to assess in vivo binding of a DNA-binding domain (bait) and DNA target site (prey).

data.rdfs:label: chain termination sequencing evidence
data.rdfs:comment: Chain termination sequencing, also called Sanger sequencing after its developer, uses dideoxynucleotide triphosphates (ddNTPs) as DNA chain terminators. Single-stranded DNA template, DNA primer, DNA polymerase, fluorescently or radioactively labeled nucleotides, and one of four ddNTPs are added together in each of four separate sequencing reactions. The synthesized and labeled DNA fragments from each of the four reactions are denatured, separated by size by gel electrophoresis, and visualized by autoradiography or UV light.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A nucleotide sequencing assay result derived by the chain termination sequencing method.

data.rdfs:label: compositional similarity evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: Used when an annotation is made based on the similarity of the histological makeup of structures.

data.rdfs:label: gel electrophoresis evidence
data.rdfs:comment: Molecules typically separated include DNA, RNA, or protein. The gel is typically made of agarose, polyacrylamide, or starch.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of direct assay evidence  where molecules have been sorted according to their size and charge by moving through a gel in the presence of an electric field.

data.rdfs:label: protein expression level evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of protein expression level analysis that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: western blot evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of Western blot assay that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: in vitro palmitoylation assay evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of in vitro palmitoylation assay evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: Northern assay evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of transcript expression level evidence based on electrophoresis and probing to determine levels of RNA expression using a complementary hybridization probe on the separated RNA samples.

data.rdfs:label: imported automatically asserted information used in automatic assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: Evidence that was initially used in automatic assertion by one person or group, which is imported by a second person or group and used in automatic assertion.

data.rdfs:label: restriction landmark genomic scanning evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of restriction landmark genome scanning evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: phylogenetic determination of loss of key residues evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of phylogenetic determination of loss of key residues evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: surface plasmon resonance evidence
data.rdfs:comment: Plasmons are generated by an incident light beam.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of physical interaction evidence based on real-time, rapid plasmon generation on the interface between a planar surface and vacuum that measures changes in refractive index close to the sensor surface when an analyte and its immobilized ligand bind to observe and characterize molecular interaction.

data.rdfs:label: competitive growth assay evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of biological assay evidence in which a mutated strain of a microorganism, such as a yeast or bacterium, is grown competitively with wild-type cells and the relative fitness of the strains is assessed.

data.rdfs:label: mutant physiological response evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: Used when an annotation is made based on the physiological response of a mutant to an external stimulus; for example, abnormal growth of the root in response to gravity, delay in flowering in response to varying light conditions.

data.rdfs:label: wound healing assay evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of wound healing assay evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: 454 pyrosequencing evidence
data.rdfs:comment: 454 pyrosequencing technology amplifies individual DNA fragments inside water droplets within an oil solution (emulsion PCR). Within each droplet, a single DNA template is attached to a single primer-coated bead. Each bead is subsequently captured in a picolitre well within the sequencing machine. A luciferase-based readout system is used to identify individual nucleotides added to the nascent DNA.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A high throughput nucleotide sequencing result derived by 454 pyrosequencing technology.

data.rdfs:label: epitope-tagged protein immunolocalization evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: Used when an annotation is made based on immunolocalization of recombinant proteins fused with epitopes that are recognized by antibodies.

data.rdfs:label: adhesion assay evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of adhesion assay evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: DNA microarray evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of DNA microarray evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: point mutation evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of point mutation evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: in vitro cell based assay evidence
in vivo cell staining evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of in vivo assay evidence in which living cells are stained with a vital stain, i.e. dye that can be used on living cells without causing cell death.

data.rdfs:label: two-dimensional polyacrylamide gel electrophoresis evidence
data.rdfs:comment: Two-dimensional polyacrylamide gel electrophoresis is commonly employed to establish a proteome for an organism and demonstrate expression changes.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of gel electrophoresis beginning with one dimension electrophoresis where biomolecules are electrophoresed on a low percentage polyacrylamide gel  to be separated in proportion to their mass or isoelectric point, followed by high voltage electrophoresis on a higher percentage gel in the presence of ethidium bromide to alter non-linear molecular shape.

data.rdfs:label: chromosome conformation capture sequencing evidence
data.rdfs:comment: 3C-seq is used to study the structural properties and spatial organization of chromosomes inside cells. Like other types of chromosome conformation capture technology, 3C-seq differs only in the fifth step, which involves inverse polymerase chain reaction (PCR) on a circularized 3C library prior to product quantitation.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of chromosome conformation capture-based evidence that is derived by inverse polymerase chain reaction (inverse PCR) on a circularized 3C library prior to product quantitation with high-throughput (HT) sequencing.

data.rdfs:label: expression pattern evidence
data.rdfs:comment: Use this evidence type when the annotation is inferred from the timing or location of expression of a gene. It may be difficult to determine whether the expression pattern truly indicates that a gene plays a role in a given process.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: Experimental evidence that is based on characterization of gene expression.

data.rdfs:label: enzyme assay evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: Used when an annotation is made based on assays that determine the catalytic activity of enzymes.

data.rdfs:label: caspase assay evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of caspase assay evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: Illumina sequencing evidence
data.rdfs:comment: In Illumina sequencing technology, adapters are ligated onto the ends of randomly fragmented DNA. After single-stranded fragments are bound to the inside surface of a flow cell channel, they undergo in-place bridge PCR amplification. To begin the sequencing cycle, labeled reversible terminators, primers and DNA polymerase are added, followed by laser excitation of the fluorescent label and high resolution scanning. After non-incorporated nucleotides are washed away and the dye is chemically removed, the next cycle repeats with four labeled reversible terminators, primers and DNA polymerase, again followed by imaging.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A high throughput nucleotide sequencing result derived by Illumina (Solexa) sequencing technology.

data.rdfs:label: author statement used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of author statement that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: alkaline phosphatase reporter gene assay evidence
data.rdfs:comment: Alkaline phosphatase reporter assay produces a hybrid protein with alkaline phosphatase activity following transportation across the cellular membrane.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of reporter gene assay evidence based on the fusion of selected genes with the phoA gene to express alkaline phosphatase in periplasmic space for protein tracing.
oboInOwl:hasRelatedSynonym: Secreted Embryonic Alkaline Phosphatase reporter assay

data.rdfs:label: DNA microarray evidence
data.rdfs:comment: The mRNA extraction is performed in induced and non-induced cells and reverse transcribed with different fluorophore labeling for controls and experiment. Fluorescence is measured at two different wavelengths and the ratio between the two fluorescence intensities corresponds to the induction level.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of DNA detection assay evidence where complimentary ssDNA is attached to a solid glass, silicon, or plastic surface and is hybridized with a labeled sample of extracted mRNA or amplified cDNA and stimulated with a laser for fluorescence detected with a scanner.

data.rdfs:label: [3H]arachidonic acid release assay evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of [3H]arachidonic acid release assay evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: DNA affinity chromatography evidence
data.rdfs:comment: Biotinylation is commonly used for labeling and beads are commonly used as the matrix. Bound protein will remain attached to the beads. Results can be detected through gel electrophoresis and then sequenced by mass-spectrometry. This technique can be used to demonstrate binding of a purified protein, or to purify the binding protein from crude extract or protein mixture.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of chromatography evidence where immobilized promoter DNA is labeled and bound to a matrix through which a protein mixture is poured and then eluted to purify specific DNA binding proteins.

data.rdfs:label: computationally derived logical inference from automatic assertion used in automatic assertion
physical interaction evidence
data.rdfs:comment: Molecules interacted with might include protein, nucleic acid, ion, or complex.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: Experimental evidence that is based on characterization of an interaction between a gene product and another molecule.

data.rdfs:label: cytochemistry evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of cytochemistry evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: differential gene expression evidence from RNA-seq experiment
in vivo acetylation assay evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of in vivo acetylation assay evidence that is used in manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: chromatin immunoprecipitation-chip evidence
data.rdfs:comment: A fixating agent such as formaldehyde is used to cross link proteins and DNA. Sonication is applied for DNA shearing. For transcription factor tagging, an antibody or epitope is employed. After cross-linking is reversed, the DNA is amplified and labeled with a flourophore for microarray which produces a resolution of aproximately 500 bp.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of chromatin immunoprecipitation (ChIP) evidence that uses a tiling microarray for the detection of protein-bound DNA regions where chromatin is immunoprecipitated for protein tagging and DNA is sheared from the cross-linked protein-DNA complex to be arrayed revealing the protein-bound genomic regions.

data.rdfs:label: consensus search evidence
data.rdfs:comment: This technique is used to identify transcription factor binding sites by searching a bacterial genome for DNA regions resembling a given TF-binding motif. PMID: 17085555.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of motif similarity evidence where the motif is represented by a consensus sequence which incorporates the most frequent nucleotide at each position acting as a generic representative for the sequences in the alignment, and is compared to the genetic sequence  for a perfect or imperfect match.

data.rdfs:label: TACE activity assay evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of TACE activity assay evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: chromatin immunoprecipitation- exonuclease evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of chromatin immunoprecipitation evidence that uses gama-exonuclease to digest TF-unbound DNA after ChIP for the identification of transcription factor binding site locations with high-resolution data.

data.rdfs:label: in situ hybridization evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: Used when an annotation is made based on a method that hybridizes a labeled nucleic acid probe to a tissue or cell specimen in which the cellular structures are still intact. Depending on the label and protocol used, the probe may detect complementary DNA or RNA by hybridizing specifically to that gene or sequence.

data.rdfs:label: histochemistry evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of histochemistry evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: similarity evidence used in automatic assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: Similarity evidence that is used in an automatic assertion.

data.rdfs:label: biological system reconstruction evidence by experimental evidence from single species
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of biological system reconstruction where the experimental evidence is derived by using multiple experiments in a single species.

data.rdfs:label: biological system reconstruction evidence based on orthology evidence
data.rdfs:comment: Inference is made primarily on functional conservation between the two systems. The sequences and number of genome-encoded components are fairly conserved but some divergence is observed. Evidence may originate from a combination of several experiments.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of biological system reconstruction evidence based on homology evidence where the evidence is inferred by orthology from an existing experimentally supported model to a process, pathway or complex in another species.

data.rdfs:label: specific protein inhibition evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of protein assay evidence based on the inhibition of the molecular function of a protein.

data.rdfs:label: crystallography evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of crystallography evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: tissue grafting evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of anatomical perturbation that is based on adding tissue to an organism through a graft procedure.

data.rdfs:label: phylogenetic distribution evidence
data.rdfs:comment: Example of use: "The presence of paired evaginated hemispheres and olfactory bulbs in both agnathan and gnathostome radiations suggests that such hemispheres were also present in the common ancestor." PMID: 7013637. Northcutt RG. (1981) Evolution of the telencephalon in nonmammals. Ann. Rev. Neurosci.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of phylogenetic evidence characterized by the mapping of the character states of living organisms onto phylogenies using the method of maximum parsimony.

data.rdfs:label: survival analysis evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of knockout evidence based on the survival of an organism in a particular environment where a gene for an enzyme or regulator is knocked out and results are used as a natural reporter.

data.rdfs:label: functional complementation evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: Used when an annotation is made based on a functional complementation assay in which a wild-type copy of the gene in question is inserted into a mutant background in the organism of the gene's origin or a heterologous organism with a mutation in the homologous gene.

data.rdfs:label: co-localization evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of co-localization evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: in vivo defarnesylation assay evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of in vivo assay evidence where removal of farnesyl groups from a protein is detected in cells in vivo.

data.rdfs:label: motif discovery evidence
data.rdfs:comment: Relationship type between sequences (e.g. orthologs from multiple genomes or co-expressed genes in the same genome) is not necessarily assumed. The local multiple sequence alignment is typically ungapped. A common application of motif discovery is to infer the binding motif of a given transcription factor (TF). This can be based on the results of a whole-genome expression analysis, assuming that co-expressed genes are co-regulated by the same TF (PMID: 19892760), from peaks in ChIP-seq experiments with the TF (PMID: 16264194), or from the comparative genomics analysis of the promoter regions of orthologs (PMID: 23032607).
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of sequence alignment evidence based on a set of algorithms that infer over-represented motifs from a set of biological sequences returning one or more local multiple sequence alignment defining the inferred motifs.

data.rdfs:label: specific protein inhibition by antibody evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of specific protein inhibition evidence where the molecular function of a protein is inhibited by an antibody.

data.rdfs:label: in vitro desumoylation assay evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of in vitro assay evidence where the removal of sumo groups is detected on a protein in vitro.

data.rdfs:label: biological aspect of ancestor evidence
data.rdfs:comment: First, a characteristic of the most recent common ancestor (MRCA) is inferred from experimental evidence in descendants; this is followed by inferring a characteristic of a descendant of the MRCA. This type of evidence can be used in support of both positive and "not" GO annotations.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of phylogenetic evidence whereby an aspect of a descendant gene is inferred through the characterization of an aspect of an ancestral gene.

data.rdfs:label: annexin-V staining evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of annexin-V staining evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: macroscopy evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of macroscopy evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: RNA protection assay evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of nuclease protection assay evidence used for transcription start-site localization where mRNA is hybridize with radiolabeled RNA probes after which RNAse is added to digest the unbound, nonresistant single-stranded overhang regions and the resistant fragment size and identity is determined with gel electrophoresis.

data.rdfs:label: gene neighbors evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of gene neighbors evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: RNA sequencing assay evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of nucleotide sequencing assay evidence where RNA is extracted from a cell, reverse transcribed to cDNA, and sequenced for a snapshot of an organism's transcriptome with precise measurement of transcript levels and their isoforms.

data.rdfs:label: in vivo demethylation assay evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of in vivo demethylation assay evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: in vivo deacetylation assay evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of in vivo assay evidence where the removal of acetyl groups from a compound is detected in cells in vivo.

data.rdfs:label: automatic assertion
data.rdfs:comment: An automatic assertion is based on computationally generated information that is not reviewed by a person prior to making the assertion. For example, one common type of automatic assertion involves creating an association of evidence with an entity based on commonness of attributes of that entity and another entity for which an assertion already exists. The commonness is determined algorithmically.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: An assertion method that does not involve human review.

data.rdfs:label: similarity evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: An evidence type that is based on comparing likeness of distinct biological entities.

data.rdfs:label: Affymetrix array experiment evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of Affymetrix array experiment evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: in vitro deacetylation assay evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of in vitro deacetylation assay evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: no biological data found used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of no biological data found that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: in vitro protein kinase assay evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of in vitro assay evidence where phosphorylated residues in a protein are detected in an in vitro experiment.

data.rdfs:label: motif similarity evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: Motif similarity evidence that is employed in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: mutant phenotype evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of mutant phenotype evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: RNA dot blot assay evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of RNA dot blot assay evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: evidence based on computational logical inference
data.obo:IAO_0000115:
A type of inferential evidence based on a computationally derived unary inference or an inference chain in which at least one step is 
computationally derived.

data.rdfs:label: in vivo phosphatase assay evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of in vivo assay evidence where the removal of phosphate groups on a protein is detected in cells in vivo.

data.rdfs:label: in vitro sumoylation assay evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of in vitro assay evidence where sumoylated residues are detected on a protein in an in vitro experiment.

data.rdfs:label: nuclease protection assay evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of nuclease protection assay evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: coding sequence splice pattern evidence
data.rdfs:comment: This term is used by the NCBI Reference Sequences (RefSeq) in support of sequences that match the splice pattern of a coding sequence (CDS) annotated on a RefSeq, but for which full transcript information is unavailable. For sequences that have the same splice pattern as a whole RefSeq transcript, use the evidence term ECO:0000327 or a child.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of transcript splice pattern evidence that is based on the exon combination of a coding sequence (CDS), a sub-feature of a whole transcript.

data.rdfs:label: co-immunoprecipitation evidence
data.rdfs:comment: If performing GO annotation, the interacting protein is referenced in the evidence_with column.

data.rdfs:label: knockout evidence used in manual assertion

data.rdfs:label: inferential evidence
data.rdfs:comment: Inference is the process of deriving logical conclusions from premises known or assumed to be true, or alternatively, arriving at conclusions via some non-logical means of observation of patterns of facts, which can result in identifying new meanings and contexts for understanding. Given the evidence provided by a set of premises, deductive reasoning involves drawing conclusions that necessarily follow, i.e. are certain, whereas inductive reasoning generates conclusions that are likely to be, but are not necessarily, true.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of evidence where an assertion is derived from another assertion via logical inference or some non-logical but rational means.

data.rdfs:label: in vivo palmitoylation assay evidence

data.rdfs:label: nuclear magnetic resonance spectroscopy evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of nuclear magnetic resonance spectroscopy evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: ex vivo assay evidence

data.rdfs:label: cytochalasin experiment evidence
data.rdfs:comment: Cytochalasin inhibits cytokinesis by blocking the formation of contractile microfilaments.

data.rdfs:label: yeast 2-hybrid evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: Used when an annotation is based on the interaction between two proteins in a yeast two-hybrid assay. The assay involves screening a trap-tagged library with a bait-tagged vector. The library is tagged with a DNA-binding domain (trap) and the bait is tagged with a transcriptional activation domain. Interaction between a library-trap protein and the bait results in activation of a yeast reporter gene whose transcription can be experimentally assayed.

data.rdfs:label: blocking monoclonal antibody evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of blocking monoclonal antibody evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: substance quantification evidence
data.rdfs:comment: Two examples of substance quantification assay are (i) measuring how much of a radiolabelled compound is taken up by a cell and (ii) measuring how much of a substrate is turned over by a given enzyme.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of direct assay evidence where the quantity of a substance used as part of an assay is measured.

data.rdfs:label: radioisotope assay evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of radioisotope assay evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: protein BLAST evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: BLAST evidence from aligning amino acid or translated nucleotide sequence with amino acid or translated nucleotide sequence.

data.rdfs:label: Nimblegen array evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of evidence arising from a Nimblegen array experiment that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: gene neighbors evidence
data.rdfs:comment: Genomic cluster analyses include synteny and operon structure.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: Evidence that supports the identity of a gene product on the basis of the identity of neighboring genes.

data.rdfs:label: protein-binding microarray evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of oligonucleotide microarray evidence that detects binding of a tagged protein to an array of oligonucleotide probes representing potential binding sites.

data.rdfs:label: physical examination evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of physical examination evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: microarray RNA expression level evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: Used when an annotation is made based on levels of RNA expression determined by microarray experiment.

data.rdfs:label: rapid divergence from ancestral sequence evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of rapid divergence from ancestral sequence evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: microscopy evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of microscopy evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: far-Western blotting evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: Used when an annotation is based on the interaction of protein with another in a far-Western assay. The assay involves separating target proteins on an SDS-PAGE gel, blotting to a membrane, hybridization with a protein probe and visualization using a probe-directed antibody. The interacting protein is referenced in the evidence_with column.

data.rdfs:label: systematic evolution of ligands by exponential amplification evidence
data.rdfs:comment: SELEX begins with the synthesis of a large oligonucleotide library, either single-stranded DNA or RNA, which consists of random fixed-length sequences flanked by constant 5' and 3' ends that serve as primers. The library is exposed to a target ligand, typically a protein or small organic compound. Unbound sequences are removed, typically with affinity chromatography. Bound sequences are eluted and the nucleic acid is extracted, followed by PCR amplification (RNA is first reverse transcribed). PCR product is converted to single stranded (DNA) or transcribed (RNA). Oligonucleotides are bound to the ligand again and the process is repeated with increasing elution stringency. After several rounds of the process, recovered oligonucleotides are sequenced and analyzed to reveal the binding specificity of the protein.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of evidence arising from a physical interaction analysis where a combinatorial chemistry technique is used to identify oligonucleotides that bind to a target ligand.

data.rdfs:label: protein separation followed by direct sequencing evidence
data.oboInOwl:hasRelatedSynonym: IDA: protein separation and direct sequencing

data.rdfs:label: Hi-C evidence
data.rdfs:comment: Hi-C is used to study the structural properties and spatial organization of chromosomes inside cells. Hi-C is similar to other types of chromosome conformation capture technology, but involves the addition of biotinylated nucleotides during the second or fourth step and enrichment for ligated fragments using immunoprecipitation after the fourth step.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of chromosome conformation capture-based evidence that is derived by performing immunoprecipitation enrichment of ligated fragments events prior to product quantitation.

data.rdfs:label: immunofluorescence evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of protein detection assay evidence where a fluorescently labeled antibody is used to detect the presence or localization of a biomolecule within a cell.

data.rdfs:label: SOLiD sequencing evidence
data.rdfs:comment: SOLiD sequencing technology is based on sequencing by ligation. After library preparation, emulsion PCR and bead enrichment are performed, including 3' modification of templates on selected beads to allow covalent bonding to a slide. 3' modified beads are attached to a glass slide and primers are added. Four fluorescently labeled di-base probes are added and multiple cycles of ligation, detection and cleavage are performed. The number of cycles determines read length. After a number of ligation cycles, the extension product is removed and another round of ligation cycles is performed with a new primer complimentary to the n-1 position of the template. Five rounds of primer reset are performed for each sequence tag.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A high throughput nucleotide sequencing result derived by SOLiD sequencing technology.

data.rdfs:label: tissue microarray evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of tissue microarray evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: high throughput nucleotide sequencing assay evidence

data.rdfs:label: subtractive hybridization evidence

data.rdfs:label: in vitro ubiquitination assay evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of in vitro ubiquitination assay evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: heteronuclear single quantum coherence spectroscopy evidence
data.rdfs:comment: Chemical shifts in the spectrum indicating binding can be detected from analysis of a protein spectrum in the presence or absence of its cognate DNA binding site.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of nuclear magnetic resonance based on two-dimensional NMR for elucidation of the chemical structure of an isolated or synthesized chemical compound where the characteristic transfer magnetization of a proton to a nitrogen or carbon isotope is monitored by NMR, generating a specific peak in the spectrum.

data.rdfs:label: WST-1 assay evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of WST-1 assay evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: animal model system study evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of experimental evidence arising from the investigation of an animal model system.

data.rdfs:label: sequence similarity evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: Sequence similarity evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: biological system reconstruction evidence by experimental evidence from mixed species
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of biological system reconstruction evidence where the experimental evidence is derived by using a mix of species used in the same experiment.

data.rdfs:label: whole transcript splice pattern evidence used in automatic assertion
data.rdfs:comment: This term is used by the NCBI Reference Sequences (RefSeq) in support of sequences that have the same splice pattern as a RefSeq transcript. If such full transcript information is not available, RefSeq reports sequences that match the splice pattern of a coding sequence (CDS) annotated on a RefSeq, supported by the evidence term ECO:0000328 or a child.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of transcript splice pattern evidence that is based on the exon combination of a whole transcript, rather than its constituent features, and is used in automatic assertion.

data.rdfs:label: 51Cr release assay evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of 51Cr release assay evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: in vivo sumoylation assay evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of in vivo sumoylation assay evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of cross-linking evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of in vitro translation assay evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: constitutively active mutant evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of constitutively active mutant evidence that is used a in manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: cell fractionation evidence

data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of fractionation evidence where sub-cellular components are separated based on their physical properties such as density in a sucrose density gradient.

data.rdfs:label: carbon-copy chromosome conformation capture evidence
data.rdfs:comment: 5C is used to study the structural properties and spatial organization of chromosomes inside cells. Like other types of chromosome conformation capture technology, 5C differs only in the fifth step, which involves ligation-mediated amplification (LMA) followed by product quantitation.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of chromosome conformation capture-based evidence that is derived by performing ligation-mediated amplification (LMA) prior to product quantitation.

data.rdfs:label: bromodeoxyuridine incorporation assay evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of BrdU incorporation assay evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: xylE reporter gene assay evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of reporter gene assay evidence based on the fusion of the xylE gene to a specific promoter for the expression of catechol 2,3-dioxygenase that converts the colorless catechol substrate to yellow 2-hydroxymuconic semialdehyde for identification of the expression of a particular gene.

data.rdfs:label: in vitro demethylation assay evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of in vitro assay evidence where the removal of methyl groups from a compound is detected in an in vitro experiment.

data.rdfs:label: beta-galactosidase protein immunolocalization evidence
data.rdfs:comment: This term describes immunolocalization of the protein; to describe transcriptional activation, use the term "localization of LacZ transcript".
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of immunolocalization evidence that was generated using LacZ protein as a marker.

data.rdfs:label: plasmid maintenance assay evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: Experimental evidence from an assay in which a mitotically stable plasmid (or minichromosome) is introduced into cells, cells are grown without selection for several generations, the proportion of cells that retain the plasmid is then determined (by comparing colony numbers on selective versus non-selective media), and the loss per generation calculated.

data.rdfs:label: anion-exchange chromatography evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of anion-exchange chromatography evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: random mutagenesis evidence
data.rdfs:comment: Random mutagenesis is not often used in TF-binding site determination; however, it is sometimes used to investigate the effect of mutations in TF binding domains in conjunction with expression assays. Random mutations can also be introduced via chemicals, error-prone PCR (EP-PCR), degenerate oligonucleotides-Pfu(DOP), UV irradiation, mutator strains, nucleotide analogs, or DNA recombination.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of experimental phenotypic evidence where radiation or a DNA-damaging agent in vivo, or PCR with degenerate primers in vitro are used for non-targeted mutagenesis.

data.rdfs:label: beta-glucuronidase fusion protein localization evidence

data.rdfs:label: physical interaction evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of physical interaction evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: ectopic expression evidence

data.rdfs:label: rapid amplification of cDNA ends polymerase chain reaction evidence
data.rdfs:comment: RACE PCR is frequently used to verify transcription start sites relevant to the function of transcription factor binding sites such as repression.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of polymerase chain reaction evidence used to obtain the full length sequence of a RNA transcript where a mRNA primer is used for RT-PCR and terminal deoxynucleotidyl transferase (TdT) is used to add identical nucleotides to the 3' end of the cDNA after which PCR with a different primer and TdT-oligomer are performed in the other sense.

data.rdfs:label: conditional knockout evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of conditional knockout evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: in vitro sumoylation assay evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of in vitro sumoylation assay evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: in vivo cleavage assay evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of in vivo assay evidence where the cleavage of a protein by a protease is detected in cells in vivo. The cleavage gives rise to protein fragments.

data.rdfs:label: in vitro methylation assay evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of in vitro methylation assay evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: in vitro defarnesylation assay evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of in vitro assay evidence where the removal of farnesyl groups from a protein is detected in an in vitro experiment.

data.rdfs:label: inference from background scientific knowledge used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of inference from background scientific knowledge that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: luciferase reporter gene assay evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of reporter gene assay evidence where luciferase, an oxidative enzyme, is used as the reporter to detect a gene product with bioluminescence.

data.rdfs:label: traceable author statement
data.rdfs:comment: The traceable author statement (TAS) evidence code covers author statements that are attributed to a cited source. Typically this type of information comes from review articles. Material from the introductions and discussion sections of non-review papers may also be suitable if another reference is cited as the source of experimental work or analysis. When annotating with this code the curator should use caution and be aware that authors often cite papers dealing with experiments that were performed in organisms different from the one being discussed in the paper at hand. Thus a problem with the TAS code is that it may turn out from following up the references in the paper that no experiments were performed on the gene in the organism actually being characterized in the primary paper. For this reason we recommend (when time and resources allow) that curators track down the cited paper and annotate directly from the experimental paper using the appropriate experimental evidence code. When this is not possible and it is necessary to annotate from reviews, the TAS code is the appropriate code to use for statements that are associated with a cited reference. Once an annotation has been made to a given term using an experimental evidence code, we recommend removing any annotations made to the same term using the TAS evidence code.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: An author statement that is based on a cited reference.

data.rdfs:label: site-directed mutagenesis evidence
data.rdfs:comment: Site-directed mutagenesis is often performed in tandem with EMSA. It is often implemented only in conserved motif positions or serially through all positions of a site.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of experimental phenotypic evidence based on target-specified mutagenesis for the characterization of various gene and protein interactions, structures, and functions where oligonucleotide primers are used to alter a nucleotide sequence.

data.rdfs:label: gel-filtration evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of gel-filtration evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: match to sequence model evidence used in automatic assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A match to sequence model evidence that is employed in an automatic assertion.

data.rdfs:label: biological system reconstruction evidence based on orthology evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of biological system reconstruction evidence based on orthology evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: hybrid interaction evidence
data.rdfs:comment: Typically enzymes which confer resistance to antibiotics, such as Dihydrofolate reductase or Beta-lactamase, or proteins that give colorimetric or fluorescent signals are used. The Bait protein is generally the protein under study and the methods are readily adaptable to highthroughput mode.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of affinity evidence where proteins of interest (bait and prey) are covalently linked to incomplete fragments of a third protein (reporter) and expressed in vivo, at which time interaction between bait and prey proteins brings reporter fragments in close enough proximity to allow them to reform and become a functional reporter protein.

data.rdfs:label: DNA laddering assay evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of DNA laddering assay evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: tissue ablation evidence
data.rdfs:comment: A tissue ablation experiment involves observing the phenotype of an entity whose tissues have been disrupted through genetic or biochemical manipulation, physical destruction, or some other means.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of anatomical perturbation that is based on disruption of tissue.

data.rdfs:label: hydroxyl-radical footprinting evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of nucleic acid binding evidence used to identify protein-binding sites on the DNA molecule where DNA that has been bound to protein is digested with hydroxyl radical produced by reduction of hydrogen peroxide with iron (II), followed by separating the cleavage products on a denaturing electrophoresis gel.

data.rdfs:label: in vitro farnesylation assay evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of in vitro farnesylation assay evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: experimental evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of experimental evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: immunohistochemistry evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of immunohistochemistry evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: match to sequence model evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A match to sequence model evidence that is employed in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: computational image-based phenotypic evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of phenotypic evidence based on unsupervised computational examination of a visual mutant phenotype such as abnormalities in organism morphology.

data.rdfs:label: imported information used in automatic assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of imported information that is used in an automatic assertion.

data.rdfs:label: deletion evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of deletion evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: knockin evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of knockin evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: in vivo ubiquitination assay evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of in vivo assay evidence where ubiquitinated residues on a protein are detected in cells in vivo.

data.rdfs:label: phylogenetic determination of loss of key residues evidence

data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of phylogenetic evidence characterized by the absence of key sequence residues.

data.rdfs:label: in vivo methylation assay evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of in vivo assay evidence where methylated residues are detected in a compound (such as a protein or a nucleic acid) in vivo.

data.rdfs:label: microarray RNA expression level evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of microarray RNA expression level data that is used in manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: ultraviolet light footprinting evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of nucleic acid binding evidence where DNA is non-specifically fragmented with ultraviolet light while protein-bound regions are protected from UV damage and strand breakage patterns are analyzed by PAGE and sequenced to detect protein-DNA contacts.

data.rdfs:label: in vivo defarnesylation assay evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of in vivo defarnesylation assay evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: double mutant phenotype evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: Used when an annotation is made based on the phenotype of double mutant organism that contains a mutation in the gene product of interest in addition to a second mutation at an unrelated locus.

data.rdfs:label: in vitro cleavage assay evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of in vitro cleavage assay evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: match to sequence model evidence
data.rdfs:comment: Used when evidence from any kind of statistical model of a sequence or group of sequences is used to make a prediction about the function of a protein or RNA. Examples of relevant evidence are: Hidden Markov Models, PROSITE motifs, and tools such as tRNASCAN.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: Sequence similarity evidence that is based on a sequence-based statistical model that predicts the function of a gene product.

data.rdfs:label: array experiment evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of array experiment evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: in vitro phosphatase assay evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of in vitro assay evidence where the removal of phosphatase groups on a protein is detected in an in vitro experiment.

data.rdfs:label: natural variation mutant evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of natural variation mutant evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: in vivo polyADP-ribosylation assay evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of in vivo polyADP-ribosylation assay evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: cleavage arrested development evidence
data.rdfs:comment: In the embryos of some organisms, inhibition of cytokinesis blocks neither the cell cycle nor the unfolding of the developmental program. As such, embryonic morphology can be frozen, allowing analysis of the developmental fate of each cell present at the time of cleavage arrest.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of experimental phenotypic evidence where embryonic development proceeds although cytokinesis is blocked.

data.rdfs:label: induced mutation evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of induced mutation evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: chromatin immunoprecipitation-seq evidence
data.rdfs:comment: ChIP-Seq experiments often use the input as a control to eliminate biases. To obtain similar results, ChIP-chip with high-density tiling arrays can be used.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A chromatin immunoprecipitation (ChIP) evidence that uses high-throughput sequencing where immunoprecipitated DNA fragments are funneled into a massively parallel sequencer to produce multiple short reads for locating binding sites of DNA-associated proteins.

data.rdfs:label: developmental similarity evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: Used when an annotation is made based on the similarity of embryological and/or post-embryonic origin of structures.

data.rdfs:label: clinical study evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of experimental evidence arising from a controlled investigation that uses human subjects.

data.rdfs:label: rapid divergence from ancestral sequence evidence
data.rdfs:comment: Long branch lengths indicate that descendant sequences may have acquired different or additional functions than the ancestral sequence.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of phylogenetic evidence characterized by long phylogenetic tree branch lengths following a duplication event.

data.rdfs:label: protein expression evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of protein expression analysis that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: computational combinatorial evidence
data.rdfs:comment: Combinatorial analyses could include experimental or computational results.
