For simple sequence comparisons, one should use the sequence similarity analysis evidence type. For microarray results alone, expression pattern analysis is appropriate; whereas, large-scale computational analysis should be used when microarray results are combined with the results of other types of large-scale experiments.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of combinatorial analysis where data are combined and evaluated by an algorithm.

data.rdfs:label: quantitative mass spectrometry evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of quantitative mass spectrometry evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: genomic microarray evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of evidence arising from a genomic microarray experiment that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: transmembrane domain prediction evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: Used when a component annotation is made based on the presence of one or more transmembrane domains in a protein's primary sequence. The presence of the transmembrane domains may be detected by computational prediction and/or the author's manual examination of the sequence.

data.rdfs:label: whole transcript splice pattern evidence
data.rdfs:comment: This term is used by the NCBI Reference Sequences (RefSeq) in support of sequences that have the same splice pattern as a RefSeq transcript. If such full transcript information is not available, RefSeq reports sequences that match the splice pattern of a coding sequence (CDS) annotated on a RefSeq, supported by the evidence term ECO:0000328 or a child.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of transcript splice pattern evidence that is based on the exon combination of a whole transcript, rather than its constituent features.

data.rdfs:label: morpholino experiment evidence
data.rdfs:comment: Morpholino oligonucleotides modify gene expression by blocking access of other molecules to specific, approximately 25-base-long regions of the base-pairing surfaces of ribonucleic acid (RNA). To achieve this anti-sense knockdown technique, delivery of the morpholino can be achieved via microinjection, electroporation, or another method.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of experimental phenotypic evidence that uses anti-sense by introducing morpholino oligonucleotides into the cytosol of a cell.

data.rdfs:label: biological aspect of descendant evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of biological aspect of descendant evidence that is used in a manual assertion.
oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym: inferred from biological aspect of descendant

data.rdfs:label: random mutagenesis evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of random mutagenesis evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: transgenic organism evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of transgenic organism evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: protein sequencing assay evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of protein sequencing assay evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: electrophoretic mobility shift assay evidence
data.rdfs:comment: EMSA is often used for assessing TF-binding with fluorophore labelling. Protein-nucleic acid complexes generally migrate at a slower rate than the corresponding non-bonded nucleic acid.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of direct assay evidence based on an electrophoretic mobility shift of macromolecules, compounds, and proteins where solutions of protein and nucleic acid are combined and the resulting mixtures are electrophoresed under native conditions through polyacrylamide or agarose gel to detect protein-nucleic acid interactions.

data.rdfs:label: anion-exchange chromatography evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of chromatography evidence where a positively charged ion exchange resin with an affinity for molecules having net negative surface charges is used to separate the molecules.

data.rdfs:label: reverse transcription polymerase chain reaction evidence
data.rdfs:comment: The starting product for PCR, and therefore amplification volume, is directly correlated to the transcription rate.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of polymerase chain reaction evidence where RNA is reverse transcribed into cDNA and amplified for product measurement in real time for transcription analysis i.e. qPCR.

data.rdfs:label: peptide affinity enrichment evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of peptide affinity enrichment evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: split-ubiquitin assay evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: Used when an annotation is based on the interaction of two proteins in a split-ubiquitin assay. The bait protein is fused to the C-terminal ubiquitin (Cub) domain followed by a reporter protein, and the prey protein is fused to a mutated N terminal ubiquiting (NubG) domain. If bait and prey interact, their interaction brings the NubG and Cub domains close enough together to reconstitute split-ubiquitin, resulting in the release of the reporter protein by the action of the UBPs.

data.rdfs:label: terminal deoxynucleotidyl transferase dUTP nick end labeling assay evidence
oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym: terminal deoxynucleotidyl transferase-dUTP nick end labeling assay evidence
TdT-mediated dUTP-biotin nick end labeling assay

data.rdfs:label: biological aspect of ancestor evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of biological aspect of ancestor evidence that is used in a manual assertion.
oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym: inferred from biological aspect of ancestor

data.rdfs:label: allograft transplantation experiment evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of anatomical perturbation evidence where an organ or tissue is transplanted from one individual to another of the same species with a different genotype.

data.rdfs:label: chromosome conformation capture-PCR evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of chromosome conformation capture evidence that is derived by performing polymerase chain reaction (PCR) in the quantitation step.

data.rdfs:label: RNA dot blot assay evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of RNA detection assay evidence based on the direct application of a RNA mixture in a circular motion on a matrix for hybridization with labeled DNA fragments.

data.rdfs:label: Full support of intron position by RNA-seq alignment evidence used in automatic assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of full support of intron position by RNA-seq alignment evidence that is used in an automatic assertion.

data.rdfs:label: particle size and count assay evidence
data.rdfs:comment: An example of an instrument used to analyze particle sizes and counts is the Beckman Coulter Z Series system.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of direct assay evidence resulting from an assay where both the size of and number of particles in a sample are determined.

data.rdfs:label: biochemical trait analysis evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: Used when an annotation is made based on the analysis of a biochemical aspect of a mutant phenotype; for example, the accumulation of a biosynthetic intermediate.

data.rdfs:label: xenotransplantation experiment evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of xenotransplantation experiment evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: experimental phenotypic evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: Experimental evidence that is based on the expression of a genotype in an environment.

data.rdfs:label: allograft transplantation experiment evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of allograft transplantation experiment evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: immunogold labelling evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of protein assay evidence that involves attaching colloidal gold particles to a secondary antibody, which is attached to a primary antibody that binds a specific protein or cell part, followed by visualization with electron microscopy.

data.rdfs:label: coding sequence splice pattern evidence used in automatic assertion
data.rdfs:comment: This term is used by the NCBI Reference Sequences (RefSeq) in support of sequences that match the splice pattern of a coding sequence (CDS) annotated on a RefSeq, but for which full transcript information is unavailable. For sequences that have the same splice pattern as a whole RefSeq transcript, use the evidence term ECO:0000327 or a child.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of transcript splice pattern evidence that is based on the exon combination of a coding sequence (CDS), a sub-feature of a whole transcript, and is used in automatic assertion.

data.rdfs:label: ectopic expression evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of ectopic expression evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: 3D cell culture evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of 3D cell culture evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: Support of intron position by RNA-seq alignment evidence used in automatic assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of support of intron position by RNA-seq alignment evidence that is used in an automatic assertion.

data.rdfs:label: evidence used in automatic assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of evidence that is used in an automatic assertion.

data.rdfs:label: co-electrophoresis evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of co-electrophoresis evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: differential hybridization evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: Used when an annotation is made based on results of a differential hybridization experiment that demonstrates expression of an RNA under one condition and not another.

data.rdfs:label: in vitro transcription assay used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of in vitro transcription assay evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: reconstitution assay evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of direct assay evidence based on reconstructing a biological sample from its disassociated state to its original state.

data.rdfs:label: circularized chromosome conformation capture evidence
data.rdfs:comment: 4C is used to study the structural properties and spatial organization of chromosomes inside cells. Like other types of chromosome conformation capture technology, 4C differs only in the fifth step, which involves inverse polymerase chain reaction (inverse PCR) on a circularized 3C library prior to product quantitation.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of chromosome conformation capture-based evidence that is derived by inverse polymerase chain reaction (inverse PCR) on a prior circularized 3C library followed by product quantitation with a microarray.

data.rdfs:label: Boyden chamber assay evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of Boyden chamber assay evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: position-specific scoring matrix motif search evidence
data.rdfs:comment: This technique is used to predict transcription factor binding sites in gene promoter regions by using a position weight matrix approach. (PMID: 15604457).
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of motif similarity evidence where the motif is represented by a position-specific frequency matrix (PSFM) that specifies the frequency of each base at each position of the motif, from which a position-specific scoring matrix (PSSM) can be derived under the framework of a log-likelihood ratio providing a scoring system based on the likelihood of a sequence given the motif, versus a genomic-frequency based null hypothesis.

data.rdfs:label: sequencing assay evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of experimental evidence where the order of molecules that constitute a biopolymer is determined.

data.rdfs:label: green fluorescent protein immunolocalization evidence
data.rdfs:comment: This term describes immunolocalization of the protein; to describe transcriptional activation, use the term "localization of green fluorescent protein transcript".
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of immunolocalization evidence data that was generated using green fluorescent protein (GFP) as a marker.

data.rdfs:label: 7-aminoactinomycin staining evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of 7-aminoactinomycin staining evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: spectrophotometry evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of spectrophotometry evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: blood test evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of direct assay evidence where a blood sample is extracted from an organism to analyze different blood components.

data.rdfs:label: biological system reconstruction evidence
data.rdfs:comment: The biological system in question might be a multi-step process or pathway or a physical complex comprising several components. The components in the experimental evidence can come from the same species or a mix of species. The experimental evidences may be only partial or weak.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of evidence that is based on a combination of experimental evidences or existing models of that system in a related species used for the reconstruction of a biological system.

data.rdfs:label: RNAi evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: Inference based on a phenotype observed when expressing an RNAi construct that includes a fragment of the gene product in a wild-type (for that gene product) background. A double-stranded RNA specifically suppresses the expression of the gene bearing its complementary sequence.

data.rdfs:label: biological system reconstruction evidence based on homology evidence
data.rdfs:comment: Inference may be based on paralogy or orthology of the genome-encoded components and is made primarily on functional conservation between the two systems. The sequences and number of genome-encoded components are fairly conserved but some divergence is observed. Evidence may originate from a combination of several experiments in the same or another species.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of biological system reconstruction where the evidence is inferred by homology based on conservation of sequence, function, and composition from an existing experimentally supported model to a process, pathway, or complex.

data.rdfs:label: sequence alignment evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: Sequence alignment evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: genomic systematic evolution of ligands by exponential amplification evidence
data.rdfs:comment: The reported sequences should always be verified for presence in the genome sequence.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of systematic evolution of ligands by exponential amplification evidence based on a restricted genomic DNA library to identify naturally occurring genomic aptamers and RNA-protein interaction networks with RNA-binding protein as bait and high-throughput sequencing.

data.rdfs:label: conditional knockin evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of conditional knockin evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: direct assay evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: Experimental evidence that is based on direct measurement of some aspect of a biological feature.

data.rdfs:label: chromosome conformation capture evidence
data.rdfs:comment: 3C is used to study the structural properties and spatial organization of chromosomes inside cells. Like other types of chromosome conformation capture technology, 3C differs only in the fifth step, which involves performing either standard polymerase chain reaction (PCR) or quantitative PCR (qPCR) for product quantitation.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of chromosome conformation capture-based evidence that is derived by performing a type of polymerase chain reaction (PCR) in the final product quantitation step.

data.rdfs:label: blood test evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of blood test evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: machine learning prediction of motif instance evidence
data.rdfs:comment: Machine learning algorithms include, but are not limited to artificial neural networks, random-forest, k-means clustering, hidden Markov models. This suite of methods can be used to identify or verify transcription factor-binding sites in genomic sequences (PMID: 15703297).
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of match to sequence model evidence which captures the application of a broad suite of supervised and unsupervised machine learning algorithms trained on known motif instances and applied to the prediction of novel putative instances of a motif in a set of biological sequences.

data.rdfs:label: in vitro protein kinase assay evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of in vitro protein kinase assay evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: in vitro deacetylation assay evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of in vitro assay evidence where the removal of acetyl groups from a compound is detected in an in vitro experiment.

data.rdfs:label: transmembrane domain prediction evidence used in automatic assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: Transmembrane domain prediction that is employed in an automatic assertion.

data.rdfs:label: beta-glucuronidase reporter gene assay evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of reporter gene assay evidence where the beta-glucuronidase enzyme from Escherichia coli is used as the reporter to transform non-fluorescent substrates into fluorescents for detection.

data.rdfs:label: nucleotide BLAST evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: Nucleotide BLAST evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: matrix-assisted laser desorption/ionization time-of-flight mass spectrometry evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of matrix-assisted laser desorption/ionization time-of-flight mass spectrometry evidence that is  used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: fluorescence resonance energy transfer evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of fluorescence resonance energy transfer evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: in vitro deubiquitination assay evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of in vitro assay evidence where the removal of ubiquitin groups on a protein is detected in vitro.

data.rdfs:label: expression library screen evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of protein expression evidence where a protein of interest is isolated on the basis of its hybridization to an antibody raised to a homologous protein.

data.rdfs:label: biological system reconstruction evidence by experimental evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of biological system reconstruction evidence that uses experimental evidence as support.

data.rdfs:label: biological system reconstruction evidence by experimental evidence from mixed species used in manual assertion
data.rdfs:comment: Inference is made primarily on functional conservation between the two systems. The sequences and number of genome-encoded components are fairly conserved but some divergence is observed. The evidence may originate from a combination of several experiments.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of biological system reconstruction evidence by experimental evidence from mixed species that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: in vivo protein kinase assay evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of in vivo protein kinase assay evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: environmental perturbation evidence
data.rdfs:comment: Many environmental factors are subject to modification, such as temperature, pressure, humidity, radiation, and so forth.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: Experimental phenotypic evidence where the extra-organismal context of an organism is modified.

data.rdfs:label: isothermal titration calorimetry evidence
data.rdfs:comment: When ITC is used to study TF, the temperature of two identical cells containing a known concentration of TF is monitored. After the ligand is added to the cells in precisely measured aliquots, the temperature difference in each cell is observed to determine target binding. This value can be used to compute the energetics of the reaction and hence, binding affinity of the TF for the DNA fragment. The thermodynamic profile that is measured includes the values of binding constant (K(a)), stoichiometry (n), and the enthalpy of binding (DeltaH(b)).
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of affinity evidence where the absorbed or released heat of a biomolecular binding event is directly measured in a reference cell and sample cell after the addition of a ligand using a microcalorimeter for a complete thermodynamic profile of the molecular interaction.

data.rdfs:label: glutathione S-transferase pull-down assay evidence
data.rdfs:comment: The recombinant protein can also be eluted following the pull-down and analyzed further with qPCR or sequencing.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of protein binding evidence where a gene is fused with the GST gene and the resulting recombinant bait protein is captured on an immobilized Glutathione affinity ligand and incubated with prey protein to identify and characterize protein-protein interactions.

data.rdfs:label: in vivo methylation assay evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of in vivo methylation assay evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: in vitro polyADP-ribosylation assay evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of in vitro polyADP-ribosylation assay evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: nucleotide BLAST evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: BLAST evidence from aligning nucleotide sequence with nucleotide sequence.

data.rdfs:label: spatial pattern of protein expression evidence
in vitro deubiquitination assay evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of in vitro deubiquitination assay evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: targeting sequence prediction evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A targeting sequence prediction that is employed in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: chloramphenicol acetyltransferase reporter gene assay evidence
data.rdfs:comment: The amount of acetylated chloramphenicol is directly proportional to the amount of CAT enzyme present.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of reporter gene assay evidence based on the fusion of the CAT gene to a specific promoter for the expression of chloramphenicol acetyltransferase which confers resistance to the chloramphenicol antibiotic.

data.rdfs:label: protein BLAST evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: Protein BLAST evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: fluorescence in situ hybridization evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of fluorescence in situ hybridization evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: in vitro cleavage assay evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of in vitro assay evidence where the cleavage of a protein by a protease is detected in an in vitro experiment. The cleavage gives rise to protein fragments.

data.rdfs:label: medical imaging evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of medical imaging evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: genetic similarity evidence used in automatic assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: Genetic similarity evidence that is used in an automatic assertion.

data.rdfs:label: affinity evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of physical interaction evidence that depends on the strength of the interaction between two entities.

data.rdfs:label: quantitative trait analysis evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of experimental phenotypic evidence where an annotation is made for a gene product that has not been cloned but is associated with a quantitative trait locus.

data.rdfs:label: anatomical perturbation evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: Experimental phenotypic evidence where a structural feature of an organism is disrupted.

data.rdfs:label: evidence based on logical inference from automatic annotation used in automatic assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of evidence based on logical inference from an automatically curated annotation that is used in an automatic assertion.

data.rdfs:label: in vivo translation assay evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of in vivo assay evidence where de novo protein synthesis is detected in cells in vivo.

data.rdfs:label: evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of evidence that is used in an manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: in vivo acetylation assay evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of in vivo assay evidence where acetylated residues are detected in a compound (such as a protein or a nucleic acid) in cells in vivo.

data.rdfs:label: carboxyfluorescein diacetate succinimidyl ester staining evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of carboxyfluorescein diacetate succinimidyl ester staining evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: sequence orthology evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: Orthology is a relationship between genes in different species indicating that the genes derive from a common ancestor. Orthology is established by multiple criteria generally including amino acid and/or nucleotide sequence comparisons and one or more of the following: phylogenetic analysis, coincident expression, conserved map location, functional complementation, immunological cross-reaction, similarity in subcellular localization, subunit structure, substrate specificity, and response to specific inhibitors.

data.rdfs:label: expression evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of expression pattern evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: curator inference used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of curator inference that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: in vitro palmitoylation assay evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of in vitro assay evidence where palmitoylated residues in proteins are detected in an in vitro experiment.

data.rdfs:label: mass spectrometry evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of mass spectrometry evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: transcript expression evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of transcript expression evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: positional similarity evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: Used when an annotation is made based on the similarity of the location and or arrangement of structures.

data.rdfs:label: in vivo ubiquitination assay evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of in vivo ubiquitination assay evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: in vivo transcription assay evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of in vivo assay evidence where transcription is detected in cells in vivo.

data.rdfs:label: biological aspect of descendant evidence
data.rdfs:comment: This type of evidence can be used in support of both positive and "not" GO annotations. It should be used to annotate ancestral genes but not extant ones.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of phylogenetic evidence whereby an aspect of an ancestral gene is inferred through the characterization of an aspect of a descendant gene.

data.rdfs:label: spatial pattern of protein expression evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of protein expression spatial pattern analysis that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: suppressor/enhancer interaction evidence
data.oboInOwl:hasRelatedSynonym: IGI: 'traditional' genetic interactions (e.g. suppressors, synthetic lethals)

data.rdfs:label: sequence alignment evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: Used when a sequence alignment is the basis for making an annotation, but only when the alignment has been manually reviewed; or if the information is in a published paper, the authors have manually reviewed the evidence. Such alignments may be pairwise alignments or multiple alignments. BLAST produces pairwise alignments and any annotations based solely on the evaluation of BLAST results should use this code.

data.rdfs:label: in vivo deubiquitination assay evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of in vivo assay evidence where the removal of ubiquitin groups on a protein is detected in cells in vivo.

data.rdfs:label: electrophysiology assay evidence
data.rdfs:comment: The scale of electrophysiology assays can range from small, e.g. a single ion channel, to large, e.g. an entire organ such as a heart.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of direct assay evidence where electrical properties of cells or tissues are studied.

data.rdfs:label: flow cytometry evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A direct assay that passes a stream of cells or particles past a light source, followed by using a detector to monitor light scatter or fluorochrome excitation to characterize the cells or particles.

data.rdfs:label: transcript splice pattern evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of sequence alignment evidence that is based on comparing the position of exon junctions, relative to a reference genome, for a transcript annotation and a supporting transcript.

data.rdfs:label: not_recorded
data.rdfs:comment: The evidence not_recorded appears in some legacy annotations; it should not be used for new annotations.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: An evidence that reflects an annotation was made before curators began tracking evidence types.

data.rdfs:label: immunodepletion evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of immunodepletion evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: imported information used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of imported information that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: in vitro transcription reconstitution assay evidence
data.oboInOwl:hasRelatedSynonym: IDA: in vitro reconstitution assay with recombinant protein

data.rdfs:label: two-dimensional agarose gel electrophoresis evidence
data.rdfs:comment: The first dimension gel is intentionally run at low voltage in low percentage agarose to separate DNA molecules in proportion to their mass. The second dimension is run at high voltage in a gel of higher agarose concentration in the presence of ethidium bromide so that the mobility of a non-linear molecule is drastically influenced by its shape.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of gel electrophoresis evidence where DNA molecules are electrophoresed on a low percentage agarose gel followed by high voltage electrophoresis on a higher percentage agarose gel in the presence of ethidium bromide.

data.rdfs:label: genomic context evidence
data.rdfs:comment: This type of evidence might include identity of neighboring genes, operon structure, synteny, phylogenetic analysis, or other whole-genome analysis.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: An evidence type that is based on the location of a gene, which gives rise to a gene product, within the genome.

data.rdfs:label: protein microarray evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of protein microarray evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: targeting sequence prediction evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: Used when a component annotation is made based on the presence of a targeting sequence in a protein's primary sequence. The presence of the targeting sequence may be detected by computational prediction and/or the author's manual examination of the sequence.

data.rdfs:label: reverse transcription polymerase chain reaction transcription evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: Used when an annotation is made based on levels of RNA expression determined by an RT-PCR experiment (quantitative or otherwise).

data.rdfs:label: chromatography evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of experimental evidence that is based on separation of constituent parts of a mixture (the mobile phase) as they pass differentially through a stationary phase due to differences in partition coefficient and retention on the stationary phase.

data.rdfs:label: multiplex bead-based immunoassay evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of multiplex bead-based immunoassay evidence that is  used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: in vivo polyADP-ribosylation assay evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of in vivo assay evidence where ADP-ribosylated residues in proteins are detected in cells in vivo.

data.rdfs:label: LacZ transcript localization evidence
data.rdfs:comment: This term describes transcriptional activation; to describe immunolocalization of the protein, use the term "immunolocalization of LacZ protein".
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A transcriptional activation assay that uses a LacZ reporter gene.

data.rdfs:label: genomic context evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of genomic context evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: chromatin immunoprecipitation-qPCR evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A chromatin immunoprecipitation (ChIP) evidence that uses quantitative polymerase chain reaction (qPCR) for DNA detection.

data.rdfs:label: yeast one-hybrid evidence
data.rdfs:comment: The assay involves screening a library of candidate proteins for the ability bind to a target, cis-regulatory element or any other short, DNA binding sequence placed 5' to a yeast reporter gene (TAIR:TED).
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of hybrid interaction evidence that is based on a protein-DNA complementation assay where a single promoter acts as bait and is screened against a library of prey transcription factors.

data.rdfs:label: sodium dodecyl sulfate polyacrylamide gel electrophoresis evidence
data.rdfs:comment: Electrophoretic mobility is a function of both the length and charge of a protein. The protein sample is linearized with sodium dodecyl sulfate (SDS), an anionic detergent. Typically, polypeptides bound with SDS possess an even distribution of charge per unit mass, and subsequent fractionation is by size.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of gel electrophoresis evidence where proteins are separated according to their electrophoretic mobility.

data.rdfs:label: spatial pattern of transcript expression evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of spatial pattern of transcript expression analysis that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: Alamar blue assay evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of Alamar blue assay evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: protein BLAST evidence used in automatic assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: Protein BLAST evidence that is used in an automatic assertion.

data.rdfs:label: fluorescence evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of protein detection by fluorescence evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: affinity chromatography evidence
data.rdfs:comment: "Used when an annotation is made based on affinity chromatography, which is a selective separation technique by which a compound (e.g., an antibody) is immobilized on a polymeric matrix and used to bind selectively other compounds. Following removal of the unattached components, the bound compound is displaced by changing the concentration of protons, salts, or cofactors in the eluent" (from original definition by TAIR:TED). Types of highly specific interaction might include those of antigen and antibody, enzyme and substrate, or receptor and ligand.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of affinity evidence that results from separation of biochemical mixtures by selective binding of a compound to an immobilized compound on a polymeric matrix, subsequent removal of unattached components, and then displacement of the bond compound.

data.rdfs:label: regular expression motif search evidence
data.rdfs:comment: Regular expression is a computational tool used for determining whether a given genome contains a DNA region resembling a transcription factor binding motif. For example A/T=W indicates A or T may be present in a column of the alignment. (PMID: 20708667).
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of motif similarity evidence where the motif, a local alignment of sequences, is represented by a regular expression, which captures the variability of nucleotides at each position in a discrete form and can then be used to search genetic sequences by identifying matches to the regular expression.

data.rdfs:label: adoptive cell transfer evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of ex vivo assay evidence derived by ex vivo selection of tumor-reactive lymphocytes, and their activation and numerical expansion before re-infusion to the autologous tumor-bearing host.

data.rdfs:label: Support of intron position by RNA-seq alignment evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of support of intron position by RNA-seq alignment evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: chimeric protein evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of chimeric protein evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: enzyme inhibition evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of specific protein inhibition evidence where the protein under study is an enzyme.

data.rdfs:label: tryptic phosphopeptide mapping assay evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of tryptic phosphopeptide mapping assay evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: RNA protection assay evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of RNA protection assay that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: cell growth assay evidence
data.rdfs:comment: Cell growth aspects can include growth rate and extent of growth. A cell growth curve acts as a natural reporter.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of in vivo assay evidence that measures one or more aspects of cell growth over a specified time period to indicate an induced or repressed regulatory effect.

data.rdfs:label: S1 nuclease protection assay evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of nuclease protection assay evidence where RNA is hybridized with complementary DNA probes and exposed to S1 nuclease for unbound RNA degradation after which the intact RNA is run on a gel for probe size determination and RNA identification to detect and map specific RNAs in a complex mixture of total cellular RNA.

data.rdfs:label: restriction fragment detection evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of restriction fragment detection evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: sequence similarity evidence used in automatic assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: Sequence similarity evidence that is used in an automatic assertion.

data.rdfs:label: immunolocalization evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of protein assay evidence that involves the use of antibodies to detect biomolecules.

data.rdfs:label: biological system reconstruction evidence by experimental evidence from single species used in manual assertion
data.rdfs:comment: Complexes shown by a single experiment should not be annotated with this term but with ECO:0000353 or a child thereof.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of biological system reconstruction evidence by experimental evidence from single species that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: anti-sense experiment evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: Used when an annotation is based on a phenotype observed when expressing an anti-sense version of a gene product in a wild-type (for that gene product) background.

data.rdfs:label: 4',6-diamidino-2-phenylindole staining evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of 4',6-diamidino-2-phenylindole staining evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: comparative genomics motif search evidence
data.rdfs:comment: This technique is used to predict transcription factor binding sites in gene promoter regions by identifying conserved DNA regions across multiple genomes. PMID: 22305460. Orthology is a typical comparative criterion used.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of motif similarity evidence based on comparative genomics which uses a search method to scan a set of genomes for instances of a specific motif, and then applies a comparative criterion to analyze the collective strength of these predictions, based on the assumption that functional instances of the motif will be preserved by natural selection and their prediction will therefore be consistent across genomes.

data.rdfs:label: in vivo deacetylation assay evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of in vivo deacetylation assay evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: chemiluminescence-linked immunoassay evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of chemiluminescence-linked immunoassay evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: primer extension assay evidence
data.rdfs:comment: The most commonly used radiolabel is 32P.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of transcript expression level evidence used to determine expression levels of mRNA where a radiolabeled synthetic oligonucleotide primer is annealed to mRNA at the transcription start site of a gene and the mRNA is extended with reverse transcriptase producing cDNA which is electrophoresed on a polyacrylamide gel and autoradiographed, and the band size is proportional to the initial RNA.

data.rdfs:label: fluorescence anisotropy evidence
data.rdfs:comment: The degree of polarization of a fluorophore is inversely related to its molecular rotation. When the fluorophore is bound to a small molecule, the rate at which it tumbles can decrease significantly from when it is bound tightly to a large protein. If the fluorophore is attached to the larger protein in a binding pair, the difference in polarization between bound and unbound states will be smaller and less accurate. The degree of binding is calculated by using the difference in anisotropy of the partially bound, free, and fully bound states measured by titrating the two binding partners. Fluorescence polarixation assays are homogeneous.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of fluorescence evidence based on rapid and quantitative analysis of diverse molecular interactions, enzyme activities, and nucleic acid hybridization which uses a fluorophore to measure the binding constants and kinetics of reactions that cause a change in the rotational time of the molecules.

data.rdfs:label: inference from background scientific knowledge
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A curator inference that links the current annotation to a different evidence-based annotation via background knowledge of the curator.

data.rdfs:label: chromosome conformation capture-based evidence
data.rdfs:comment: Chromosome conformation capture technologies are used to study the structural properties and spatial organization of chromosomes inside cells. All types of chromosome conformation capture technology involve five primary steps: cross-linking of DNA in vivo, restriction digestion, intramolecular ligation, reversing cross-linkages, and DNA enrichment and quantitation. The last step is different for each type of chromosome conformation capture technology, and may include PCR (3C), inverse PCR (4C), or ligation-mediated amplification (5C). Methods for product quantitation can include agarose gel detection or real-time quantitative PCR in the case of 3C, or high-throughput sequencing or microarray analysis for 4C and 5C.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of experimental evidence that is based on a five-step technique of cross-linking DNA in vivo, restriction digestion, intramolecular ligation, reversing DNA cross-links, and DNA processing and quantitation.

data.rdfs:label: blocking polyclonal antibody evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of blocking polyclonal antibody evidence tthat is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: in vitro acetylation assay evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of in vitro acetylation assay evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: Partial support of intron position by RNA-seq alignment evidence
data.rdfs:comment: Partial support can occur in two ways. First, one or more exon-exon pair (intron) is not supported by any RNA-seq sample included in the analysis. Second, no single RNA-seq sample provides support for all exon-exon pairs (introns) represented in a transcript, but all represented exons are supported by at least one sample.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of support of intron position by RNA-seq alignment evidence where RNA-seq alignment to a genome supports only some of the intron positions (exon pairs) predicted for a transcript.

data.rdfs:label: interferometric reflectance imaging sensor evidence
data.rdfs:comment: Differences in the optical path lengths between a surface layer and a buried silica layer can be measured very precisely allowing optical height information to be converted to accumulated mass on the surface. For the purpose of TF-binding site identification, IRIS is coupled with DNA-arrays with immobilized potential binding regions exposed to the protein of interest and eluted. Protein-bound fragments exhibit changes in reflectance that can be used to gauge binding quantitatively.
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of molecule detection assay evidence based on changes in surface-reflected light due to ligand binding on the surface of a semi-transparent substrate to detect proteins, DNA, and other biological material in a multiplexed, high-throughput microarray format without labels.

data.rdfs:label: imaging assay evidence used in manual assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of imaging assay evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

data.rdfs:label: sequence alignment evidence used in automatic assertion
data.obo:IAO_0000115: Sequence alignment evidence that is used in an automatic assertion.

data.rdfs:label: biological system reconstruction evidence based on paralogy evidence
data.obo:IAO_0000115: A type of  biological system reconstruction evidence based on homology evidence where the evidence is inferred by paralogy from an existing experimentally supported model to a process, pathway, or complex in the same species.
